Tools & Technologies -

GitHub – Version control and source code repository.

Jenkins – CI/CD automation server.

Ant – Build tool for compiling Java code.

JUnit – Unit testing framework.

Tomcat – Application server for deployment.

Pipeline Breakdown - 

1. First Job – GitHub
Pulls the latest source code from the GitHub repository.

Uses PollSCM to monitor changes in the repo.

2. Second Job – Ant
Builds the Java project using build.xml.

Compiles source code and performs quality checks.

3. Third Job – JUnit
Runs automated unit tests using JUnit.

Publishes test reports in Jenkins.

4. Fourth Job – Deploy
Deploys the final .war package to an Apache Tomcat server.

Makes the application live as the end product.

